IoT Edge Load-Aware Performance Transparency System
https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg

A simulated distributed IoT edge system that demonstrates load-aware performance transparency using Docker containers as virtual edge nodes (e.g., Raspberry Pi devices).

The system continuously monitors CPU utilisation, task load, memory usage, and response time across distributed nodes. When a node becomes overloaded, tasks are automatically migrated to underutilised nodes to maintain stable performance without modifying application logic.

This project was developed as part of the CS 535 – Distributed Systems assignment at Copperbelt University.

